      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/jacollo/{size}/780_2.png",
      "created_at": "2025-01-13T11:49:43.659Z",
      "cooked": "<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/438b78d4b5573c063522ed9fa8b9cdb4d8914f5b.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/438b78d4b5573c063522ed9fa8b9cdb4d8914f5b\" title=\"IMG_8385\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/4/438b78d4b5573c063522ed9fa8b9cdb4d8914f5b_2_375x500.jpeg\" alt=\"IMG_8385\" data-base62-sha1=\"9DwO5xrJzxBRgu8ONj57AIng8KD\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/4/438b78d4b5573c063522ed9fa8b9cdb4d8914f5b_2_375x500.jpeg, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/4/438b78d4b5573c063522ed9fa8b9cdb4d8914f5b_2_562x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/4/438b78d4b5573c063522ed9fa8b9cdb4d8914f5b_2_750x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"7E827C\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">IMG_8385</span><span class=\"informations\">3024\u00d74032 3.13 MB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>I recently purchased the Zwift Ride frame and plan to use TrainerDay as my main application with it. It would be incredibly useful if the buttons on the frame could function as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Plus/Minus for HR+</li>\n<li>Adjusting ERG intensity</li>\n<li>Modifying Slope.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Since the Zwift Frame is equipped with the Zwift Cog, and there are no mechanical gears or cassette, implementing a form of virtual gear shifting would be a fantastic addition. Perhaps this could work as a control for Resistance?</p>\n<p>I\u2019m happy to assist with testing and provide more detailed suggestions as I spend more time using the frame. Let me know if I can help make this happen!</p>",
